{
  "page": "Mystery knight",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">This is about the  type of tourney contestant. For the novella, see <a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/14/The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg/350px-The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"501\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/14/The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg/525px-The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/14/The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg/700px-The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_mystery_knight_by_grr_martin_by_marcsimonetti.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a>, by Marc Simonetti ©</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>mystery knight</b> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> who competes in a <a href=\"/index.php/Tournament\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tournament\">tournament</a> without revealing their identity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Mystery knights choose to conceal their names for a variety of reasons, and they  may or may not reveal their identity later.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> They are often popular with <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Jonquil_Darke\" title=\"Jonquil Darke\">Jonquil Darke</a> competed in the <a href=\"/index.php/War_for_the_White_Cloaks\" title=\"War for the White Cloaks\">War for the White Cloaks</a> as the Serpent in Scarlet.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelon_Targaryen_(son_of_Jaehaerys_I)\" title=\"Baelon Targaryen (son of Jaehaerys I)\">Baelon Targaryen</a> participated in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Old_Oak\" title=\"Tourney at Old Oak\">tourney at Old Oak</a> as the Silver Fool.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Viserys_II)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Viserys II)\">Aemon Targaryen</a> competed as the Knight of Tears in a tourney so he could name his sister, <a href=\"/index.php/Naerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Naerys Targaryen\">Naerys Targaryen</a>, the tournament's <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_love_and_beauty\" title=\"Queen of love and beauty\">queen of love and beauty</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> competed as the Gallows Knight during the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_tourney_at_Whitewalls\" title=\"Wedding tourney at Whitewalls\">wedding tourney at Whitewalls</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> competed as a mystery knight at the age of ten in a <a href=\"/index.php/History_of_Tourneys_in_Westeros#Tourney_at_Blackhaven\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"History of Tourneys in Westeros\">tourney at Blackhaven</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and he was knighted for again doing so at the age of sixteen in the <a href=\"/index.php/History_of_Tourneys_in_Westeros#Winter_Tourney_at_King.27s_Landing\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"History of Tourneys in Westeros\">winter tourney at King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The Bastard of Uplands competed in the <a href=\"/index.php/History_of_Tourneys_in_Westeros#Oldtown_tourney\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"History of Tourneys in Westeros\">Oldtown tourney</a> as <a href=\"/index.php/Blackshield\" title=\"Blackshield\">Blackshield</a>, but he was defeated and exposed by Barristan.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Simon_Toyne\" title=\"Simon Toyne\">Simon Toyne</a>, the infamous leader of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingswood_Brotherhood\" title=\"Kingswood Brotherhood\">Kingswood Brotherhood</a>, competed in <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Steffon%27s_tourney\" title=\"Lord Steffon&#39;s tourney\">Lord Steffon's tourney</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Storm%27s_End\" title=\"Storm&#39;s End\">Storm's End</a> as a mystery knight, where was defeated by Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar Targaryen</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> though, according to a semi-canon source, Barristan may have confused two separate tourneys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_the_Laughing_Tree\" title=\"Knight of the Laughing Tree\">Knight of the Laughing Tree</a> participated in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Harrenhal\" title=\"Tourney at Harrenhal\">tourney at Harrenhal</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/281_AC\" title=\"281 AC\">281&#160;AC</a>. King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys II Targaryen\">Aerys II Targaryen</a> tasked his son, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaegar Targaryen\">Rhaegar Targaryen</a>, with uncovering the mystery knight's identity, but all that was found was the knight's shield.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera Reed</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight_of_the_Laughing_Tree\" title=\"Knight of the Laughing Tree\">Knight of the Laughing Tree</a>, who competed in the <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney_at_Harrenhal\" title=\"Tourney at Harrenhal\">tourney at Harrenhal</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> loved it when a mystery Knight appeared at a <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourney</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Mystery knights would oft appear at <a href=\"/index.php/Tourney\" title=\"Tourney\">tourneys</a>, with helms concealing their faces, and shields that were either <a href=\"/index.php/Heraldry\" title=\"Heraldry\">blank or bore some strange device</a>. Sometimes they were famous champions in disguise.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Mystery_knight&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a hre